Suslanger
Suslanger is a part of the Khadaganian empire. Its territory is not particularly large and the inhabitable, arable area is even smaller. The river which  has gouged out a deep canyon throughout the ages flows into the lake and is practically the only significant source of water. To expand the farming lands, people have to build dams and irrigation canals. Khadaganian authorities are cruel and ruthless. Numerous guards mete out severe punishment for even the smallest deviation from the Emperor's decrees, while spies and eavesdroppers report on every person whom they find suspicious.
